<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,438,463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<number box="[333,345,439,463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
) pedestals stout, subquadrate, inner distal corner larger and roundly expanded, outer corner thinner and acute (
<figureCitation box="[362,502,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Figs. 
<number box="[426,502,475,499]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="39.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="38.0">38−40</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[523,538,475,499]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
) penis strongly developed and sclerotized, with a small spine-like projection at apex, basal 
<number box="[288,298,511,535]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[308,323,511,535]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
of penis strongly expanded dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[764,907,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Figs. 38, 40</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[930,944,511,535]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
) thumb not finger-like, reduced to a basal membrane on inner ventral margin of each penis (&quot;t&quot; in 
<figureCitation box="[776,860,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[828,860,547,571]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Male imago. Length (mm): body, 13.0− 
<number box="[647,697,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="13.5">13.5</number>
; FW, 11.0− 
<number box="[828,878,583,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="11.2">11.2</number>
; HW, 5.0− 
<number box="[1001,1038,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="5.2">5.2</number>
; cerci, 31.0; foreleg, 
<number box="[1275,1365,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="5.6" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="5.5">5.5−5.7</number>
. Body coloration completely faded. Foreleg ratio of segments in relation to femur (
<quantity box="[1061,1159,618,643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
): femur (
<number box="[1272,1284,619,643]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
), tibia (1.0), tarsomere 
<number box="[269,283,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number box="[300,339,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.1">0.1</number>
); tarsomere 
<number box="[480,495,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number box="[503,542,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.3">0.3</number>
); tarsomere 
<number box="[682,696,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[713,752,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.3">0.3</number>
), tarsomere 
<number box="[892,906,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<number box="[922,961,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.3">0.3</number>
), tarsomere 
<number box="[1101,1115,654,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<number box="[1132,1171,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.3">0.3</number>
), short claw (
<number box="[1326,1365,655,679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.2">0.2</number>
), long claw (
<number box="[219,258,691,715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="0.3">0.3</number>
). Tarsal segments 
<number box="[463,507,690,715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2−5</number>
subequal, tarsomere 
<number box="[744,758,691,715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
very short. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1148,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Figs. 
<number box="[1072,1148,691,715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="39.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="38.0">38−40</number>
</figureCitation>
): sternum IX subquadrate with rounded apical margin; pedestal stout, slightly flattened dorsoventrally, distally with large rounded inner corner and short acute outer corner (
<figureCitation box="[585,673,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[642,673,763,787]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
); penes strongly developed and sclerotized, curved ventrally and medially, finger-like on distal half, with small acute projection at apex; basal 
<number box="[1071,1081,799,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1091,1107,799,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
of penes strongly projected dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[256,385,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 − 40. C" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1760]" captionTargetBox="[163,1436,1036,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,1022,1716]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 38 − 40. C. molinai sp. nov., male adult. 38, male genitalia, v. v.; 39, pedestal, detail, v. v.; 40, penes and pedestals, v. v. (photograph). Abbreviations: ip = inner projection (pedestal); op = outer projection (pedestal); p = penes; pb = pyramidal base (penes); t = &quot; thumb &quot; (penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287909/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[309,385,835,859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" value="39.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="38.0">38−40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,870,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Discussion</emphasis>
. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[692,833,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis box="[692,833,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in genital morphology, but pedestals are stouter and penes much more developed (each lobe is very wide and large) and sclerotized. The same differences apply when compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[325,468,942,966]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahunkai">
<emphasis box="[325,468,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. mahunkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known also from 
<collectingCountry box="[678,761,942,967]" name="Bolivia" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
but here treated as synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1258,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis box="[1120,1258,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">C. truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
